1.00	2000_du_Maurier_Open	2000 du Maurier Open	The 2000 du Maurier Open was a tennis tournament played on outdoor hard courts. It was the 111th edition of the event known that year as the du Maurier Open, and was part of the Tennis Masters Series of the 2000 ATP Tour, and of the Tier I Series of the 2000 WTA Tour. The men's event took place at the National Tennis Centre in Toronto, Canada, from July 31 through August 6, 2000, and the women's event at the du Maurier Stadium in Montreal, Canada, from August 14 through August 20, 2000.	
